  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are currently buying dips as SPX trades 20 points below the GEX flip at 6577, with spot sitting in the high-gamma stabilizing zone between the 6565-6580 walls. The massive positive gamma concentration at 6580 (28.5B) creates a hard ceiling where dealers will aggressively sell any rally attempts, while the negative gamma floor at 6550 provides strong support where dealers flip to buying mode. \n\nExpect choppy, range-bound action with mean reversion bias toward the 6575-6580 zone, but watch for potential breakout acceleration if we breach 6550 to the downside where dealer buying support weakens significantly.\n\n**Key levels: 6580 resistance (dealer selling), 6577 flip point, 6550 critical support (dealer buying)**",
